Chana Aloo Curry (chickpean and potato)

3 tbsp oil
Flavor Base:
1 large onion, diced (brown, white, yellow)
2 large garlic cloves, minced
2 tbsp curry powder
1 tsp all spice powder
1 tsp nutmeg powder (or 1/2 tsp freshly grated)
1 1/2 tsp smoke paprika (can use sweet or ordinary)
2 tsp dried thyme leaves (or 3 tsp fresh thyme leaves)
1 tsp cumin powder
3/4 tsp cayenne pepper (or 1 scotch bonnet/habanero finelyt chopped, added once liquids have been added)
1 tsp white pepper
Curry:
1 1/2 c potatoes, cut into 1.2cm|1/2" cubes
2x14oz (400g) cans of chickpeas, drained
14oz (400g) canned diced tomatoes (optional)
2 c chicken stock
2 scallion sliced
2 tbsp fresh parsley, finely chopped + more for garnish (can use cilantro instead)
salt to taste

Heat oil in a large pot or very deep skillt over medium high heat. Add flavor base ingredients and cook for 3 min until the onion is translucent. Add the potatoes and cook for another 2 min. If the spices stick to bottom, add a tiny splash of water. Add the chickpeas, tomatoes, and broth. Bring to a simmer then turn down the heat to medium and simmer for 15 min, or until the potatoes are cooked and the sauce has thickened. Adjust salt to taste, stir through scallions and parsley. Serve with rice


